To create a complex pattern intertwined with a sequence of numbers, we can design a C++ program that generates a dynamic output based on a mathematical formula. The program will use nested loops and conditional logic to produce a visually appealing and mathematically structured pattern.

Here is a complete C++ program that fulfills the requirements:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <iomanip>
#include <cmath>

using namespace std;

int main() {
    int n = 10;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            if (i == j) {
                cout << "*";
            } else if (i + j == n - 1) {
                cout << "*";
            } else {
                cout << " ";
            }
        }
        cout << endl;
    }
    return 0;
}
```

